  <h1 class="title">Arnaud's technical recipes</h1>

  <p>This contains some technical information I've accumulated during
  successive employments. I decided to make it available "as is" and of course
  I disclaim any warranties related to this material. I am especially grateful
  to <a href="http://www.nag.co.uk">NAG Ltd.</a>, where I used to work, for
  allowing me to publish it.</p>

  <p>Enjoy !</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Development information

      <ul>
        <li><a href="CompilerTricks.html">Compiler and Tools Tricks</a>: more
        or less everything to get started about debugging and associated
        topic</li>

        <li><a href="Articles.html">Articles</a>: some useful articles</li>

        <li><a href="CompGdbDbx.html">Gdb vs Dbx</a>: equivalence between gdb
        and Sun dbx</li>

        <li><a href="sharedlib.html">Shared and static libraries</a>: how to
        deal with shared and static libraries</li>

        <li><a href="Version.html">Version, licence ?</a>: how to obtain the
        version and licence of a specific software</li>

        <li><a href="hardwareinfo.html">Hardware information</a>: how to obtain
        the hardware specifications</li>

        <li><a href="ManufactDoc.html">Manufacturer documentation</a>: where to
        find the manuals on the web and locally</li>

        <li>
          <a href="DevResources.html">Developer resources on-line</a>: list of
          standards available on-line

          <ul>
            <li>Eric Huss' <a href="Cstd/">The C Library Reference Guide</a>
            (with corrections)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>

        <li><a href="CVSserver.html">Setting up a CVS server</a></li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Memory debugging

      <ul>
        <li><a href="FreeMemoryDB.html">"Free" memory debuggers</a>: list of
        public domain tools related to memory debugging</li>

        <li>
          <a href="CommMemoryDB.html">Commercial memory debuggers</a>

          <ul>
            <li><a href="SunMemoryDB.html">Memory debugging capabilities on
            Sun</a></li>

            <li><a href="PC-lint.html">Notes on PC-lint</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Windows specifics

      <ul>
        <li><a href="links_windows.html">Windows Software</a>: list of useful
        public domain software for Windows</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li>Musings

      <ul>
        <li><a href="CompMuseum.html">Computer history</a></li>
      </ul>
